Yesterday, in yet another act of anti-black police violence causing mass outrage, George Floyd yelled \xe2\x80\x9cI can\xe2\x80\x99t breathe\xe2\x80\x9d and pleaded for his life as a white Minneapolis police officer violently pinned him down with his knee on his neck. George died after. He was murdered in broad daylight. His death is reminiscent of the death of Eric Garner. Even with a crowd yelling at him to stop and while folks filmed the murder, the cop did it anyway, showing the massive injustice, zero accountability and white supremacy embedded in the \xe2\x80\x9ccriminal justice\xe2\x80\x9d system. Heartbroken, angry and disgusted. This must end. Much love and solidarity to Black communities grieving another beautiful life lost. May George Floyd Rest in Power.
